title.narrative: MATERNAL NEW BORN & CHILD HEALTH

description.narrative: Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH). Quality maternal, newborn and child health services are available and demanded by families, to ensure mothers and girls and boys are healthy, especially in the most deprived areas, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved access and increased utilization of quality and equity focused Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health (MNCH) and immunization services for mothers, new born, U5 children and adolescent girls in most deprived provinces and areas
